Note:
Rust Lexer - Streaming tokenizer for Rust source code

Provides the single-token streaming API consumed by rust_parser.runa:
    create_rust_lexer(source)         -> lexer handle (primes nothing)
    next_rust_token(lexer)            -> advances to and returns the next token type
    current_rust_token_type(lexer)    -> the most recently scanned token type
    current_rust_lexeme(lexer)        -> an OWNED, NUL-terminated copy of the lexeme
    destroy_rust_lexer(lexer)         -> releases the lexer struct

Each token kind is its own constant (TOKEN_FN, TOKEN_LBRACE, ...) so the parser
can dispatch directly on the token type without re-comparing lexemes. The lexeme
copy is heap-owned so AST nodes outlive the lexer's per-token state.

Covers the full Rust 2021 lexical grammar required by the translation pipeline:
keywords, identifiers, lifetimes ('a), integer/float literals (decimal, hex,
octal, binary, suffixes, underscores), char/byte/string/raw-string literals,
the complete operator and punctuation set (incl. :: -> => ..= <<= >>= etc.),
line and block comments, and attributes (#[...] / #![...]).

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Type Constants
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Distinct per-token codes. Keywords occupy 1..49, punctuation/operators
Note: 50..149, literals/identifiers 150..169, specials 180+.

Note: Keywords
Constant TOKEN_FN as Integer is 1
Constant TOKEN_LET as Integer is 2
Constant TOKEN_MUT as Integer is 3
Constant TOKEN_PUB as Integer is 4
Constant TOKEN_STRUCT as Integer is 5
